<P><HI>Thou &s;halt victorious tread on the black Serpent, and the A&s;p: the Dragon and the Great Dragon thou &s;halt trample under foot.</HI></P></Q>
<Q><P>Melius re&s;ponderi non pote&s;t Calumnia|torum Maledicentiae quam non re&s;|pondendo.</P>
<BIBL>Melch. Adam. in Vita Bezae.</BIBL></Q>
<Q><PB N="64" REF="002143_0080_0FBC234242C313B8" MS="y">
<BIBL>A Speech of the Martyr <HI>Vineditirus.</HI></BIBL>
<P><HI>Rage and do the wor&s;t, that Malignity can &s;et thee at work to do; Thou &s;halt &s;ee the Spirit of GOD &s;trengthen the Sufferer, more than the Devil can do the Inflicter.</HI></P></Q>
